description: Never collapse multi-chord bars / walkdowns on import or charts
alwaysApply: true
---

# Multi-chord bars (walkdowns)

Global for **every** chart — e.g. UG `C G/B Am` must not become `Am`:

- `chords[]` is one string **per bar**. Several chords in the same bar are **space-separated**: `"C G/B Am"`.
- Never “pick the strongest” chord. Keep slash bass (G/B, C/E) and every printed symbol from the source.
- Engraving already splits on whitespace into beat positions (`normalize.ts`). Import AI prompt in `songs.functions.ts` must preserve this.
- `transposeChord` must transpose each token in a multi-chord bar, not the whole string as one chord.
- When fixing imports or prompts, add examples like `Dm G C G/B Am` → `["Dm","G","C","G/B Am"]` (or equivalent grouping) — all five symbols still present.
